d I will have it.  But, my tailoring is only at 103, and I want it to be at least 120 before I try it.  I spent all day on Saturday last making headys and viscous mana, and hunting threads and HQ kitty pelts.  I have a ton of stuff left to use, but used a bunch of it.  I got from 78 to 103 and it took all day!  I can hardly wait to see how long it will take me to get further, but when I hit that magical 101, I was so proud of myself.  Up till now the quest has been relatively easy.  I got all the parts I need except the blood and manes, and never sweated it at all.  Tailoring is unlike any of the other trade skills I have done so far.  I even did JC to 183 in less than a day with only 3kpp.  But tailoring, wow, tough one.  SO, when I hit 101, and looked to see master listed in the skill box, it was a great sense of accomplishment.<br>
<br>
This shawl has been very frustrating and somewhat time consuming, I will agree.  However, for me, it has become an addiction to complete it and proudly wear the shawl.  I have a bit more work to do on brewing yet and some on pottery, and then have to complete working the tailoring up, and then start fletching, but, I am having fun.  Right now, I am at:  JC 183, fletching 0, brewing 125, pottery 138, baking 142, tailoring 103, smithing 26, fishing 85.  As you can see, I have some work to do yet on a couple, but, I dont know many people who have master accomplishment at more than one trade skill.<br>
<br>
I personally will continue this quest till I have the end reward or until I give up EQ.  I hope that I get the end first, as if I dont, I shall forever feel that I left work undone.  Grats to all of you have done it and all who are trying to do it.  Keep up the work and never give up.<br>
<br>
/cheers<br>
<br>
Siene Stormwalker<br>
56th Evoker of E Marr<br>
Officer of Eternal Haven <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mudsquirt>Mudsquirt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/02 8:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Screw Shawl Quests</span><hr size=1> Why would you want to MQ these? Not only would you have the satisfaction  that youve made these yourself, but in the process achieved masterdom in every trade skill.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chiriko>chiriko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 303<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/02 1:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tailoring in hell</span><hr size=1> I think tailoring is what hell will be like, when I arrive there.. <br>
<br>
I'm not a big tradeskill fan, I do enjoy doing the occasional baking, and I've found fishing to be a fun way to meditate, but GOOD LORD tailoring is wretched. It would be one thing if just gathering the materials was difficult (Which it IS) but to also have it have the slowest rate of increase of any tradeskill I've ever seen? that's insane. I do about 40 combines for every point, and I'm only in the 30s for skill. I did shawls 1-4 at lvl 40, with very little trouble. Snow griffin's were a pain, but with some help shawls 1-4 took me about a week of casual play to finish.<br>
<br>
I've been trying to gather tailoring components to work on my 5th shawl ever since, and I'm still only in the 30s for skill. Sure, I've got a backpack full of artic wyvern hides, but fat load of good that does me. I've recently started hunting rockhoppers in DS for xp, and they've helped me fill up another backpack with hides, but most of those I won't be able to use for tailoring without slaving away making metal studs and boning. <br>
<br>
I have nothing but respect for those brave tailors out there whom have mastered the skill, but I'm afraid the patients it takes to get that far is going to break me. I'm starting to think that the people who talk about leveling twinks from 1-50 just to farm silks have the right idea.. it *would* be faster. &lt;sigh&gt;<br>
<br>
-Chiriko, lvl 53 channeler, Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=british>British</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 708<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/02 2:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> I've been working on Tailoring.  To do this requires brewing Heady Kiolas which are trivial at 46.<br>
